To install atles_web.py as a systemd service:

 1. Edit atles_web.service to set the correct values for the "User," "Group,"
    "WorkingDirectory," and "ExecStart," values in the [Service] section.

 2. Copy the atles_web.service file to /etc/systemd/system/ directory.

 3. Test running the service:
    sudo systemctl start atles_web

 4. If it works (you can access the web server with a browser), enable the service on boot:
    sudo systemctl enable atles_web


To setup a remote ATLeS box Raspberry Pi:

 1. Run "./setup_box.sh MACHINENAME" with the hostname of the Pi.

